      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BULL MUNDY (8) is a promising type who notched his 9th career success when too good (20.16) at this track last time. Has a strong winning record at this journey. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. In great recent form and expected to measure up again. LUMIERE (2) was quickly into stride and burnt early from the middle draw where he gave a sight, finishing second (20.16) and beaten 1.5 lengths over 350m at this track. Winning chance. BLUE MILK (1) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fourth (20.25) last time in a Grade 4/5 at this track. Form at the trip sound including two wins. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Can figure in the finish. WHAT'S THE PRICE (3) racing over this course and distance brings the best out in her.",
